<body>
    <h1>Azure DevOps Board (ADO)</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-m=
acro-note">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-info=
rmation-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p local-id=3D"b7fc1408-7866-48df-aa07-17e35df69669">This document has been=
 written to explain how to follow the =E2=80=98El Capitan=E2=80=99 outcome =
based team agreed Ways of Working (WoW) for Azure DevOps Board.</p>
<p local-id=3D"dc38564b-921e-44bf-bad7-6d9b34f5d963"><strong>IMPORTANT</str=
ong> - Please note ADO is not designed to replace Service Now or act as a t=
icket management system, it is being used as a tool to help visualise work =
within the =E2=80=98El Capitan=E2=80=99 outcome based team.</p>
</div>
</div>
