<h1 local-id=3D"db8c1865-af00-4f30-b849-a574822d7139" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-1.Accessingthe=E2=80=98ElCapitan=E2=80=99boardinADO">1. Accessing th=
e =E2=80=98El Capitan=E2=80=99 board in ADO</h1>
<p local-id=3D"6abaeb6a-3b76-466e-b1bc-6eb0d70cedd8"><a class=3D"external-l=
ink" href=3D"https://emisgroup.visualstudio.com/Platform%20Infrastructure%2=
0Managed%20Services%20(PIMS)/_boards/board/t/El%20Capitan/Work%20Items" rel=
=3D"nofollow">El Capitan Work Items Board - Boards</a></p>
<h2 local-id=3D"50500126-cf69-4ddb-96ce-fad0eb4b22f5" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-1.1BoardDriver">1.1 Board Driver</h2>
<p local-id=3D"d657691d-b582-4cef-94d7-bab292d1ece2">The Board Driver (BD) =
is a rotating role within the team, assigned on a weekly basis via this <a =
class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://emishealthplc.eu.pagerduty.com/sche=
dules/PPIFW8A" rel=3D"nofollow">PagerDuty Schedule</a>.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"588c6ada-ad6e-4620-acc6-cf9c0182ceba" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-Responsibilities">Responsibilities</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"134d5fd6-9886-4561-aeec-511986db2161">
<li local-id=3D"c1097688-e35a-4974-872b-4025a97d0c97">
<p local-id=3D"2785606c-a5ba-4d00-b759-a0c6761fd61a">Share the board: at th=
e beginning of each stand-up, the BD will share the Kanban board via Teams<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2ec379f6-d84c-454d-b398-cc6900fc94d4">
<p local-id=3D"3bf232ef-8631-4250-8285-685ab27e8703">Prompt discussion: sta=
rting top-to-bottom, right-to-left; the BD will prompt individuals to discu=
ss any Expedited or Tracked work items</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ec90695a-25e7-415d-a46f-1a22a167f6e7">
<p local-id=3D"810b9ceb-3857-4712-a6fd-850ef71ae67f">Keep an eye on WIP lim=
its: it=E2=80=99s everyone=E2=80=99s responsibly, but the BD should highlig=
ht when someone is currently breaching their WIP limits and prompt the indi=
vidual to fix this</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"a1d9aaed-ced5-4fad-8853-17031f27e078">Why rotate? It=E2=80=
=99s a mechanism to boost engagement with the board and foster a sense of r=
esponsibility within the team.</p>
<p local-id=3D"16c2f756-c0ba-4822-a9cc-29955029beac">What if the assigned B=
oard Driver is away? It can just be decided on-the-fly during the stand-up =
who should take on the BD role if the original person assigned is unable to=
 do it. Ideally this should not be the same person each time.</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"a26eff81-505f-463d-ab4e-de2c25c2ea94" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-1.2DailyStand-UpProcess">1.2 Daily Stand-Up Process</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"bb8719f3-e117-45e1-95b7-a1eb918804ba" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-Purpose">Purpose</h3>
<p local-id=3D"f64b8726-fc14-49b0-a49d-edadc4d781e5">Daily Stand-Up exists =
to keep work flowing by prioritising <strong>Expedite/On-Call</strong> and =
<strong>Tracked</strong> items, ensuring each has a clear owner and next ac=
tion, and maintaining board hygiene (WIP and styling rules).</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"6f79c483-6b5b-4fa0-a98d-426a0dfb389a" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-BoardDriverfacilitation">Board Driver facilitation</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"d79429f2-fab9-45ea-a400-e8ca1e3f03fd">
<li local-id=3D"83425b2c1356">
<p local-id=3D"a9f38336a601">The <strong>Board Driver</strong> shares the b=
oard at the start of stand-up.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3cb9b9788445">
<p local-id=3D"b08045894d9c">The Board Driver runs the board in a consisten=
t order: <strong>start in Expedite/On-Call</strong>, then proceed <strong>t=
op-to-bottom, right-to-left</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7f3456ce47cb">
<p local-id=3D"a8abf502b815">For each relevant work item, the Board Driver =
prompts the <strong>work item owner</strong> (Assigned To) to discuss the i=
tem.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"30373c3ab5a9">
<p local-id=3D"2d341ecdb37f">Everyone is responsible for board hygiene, but=
 the Board Driver should call out breaches (e.g., WIP/style rules) and prom=
pt the owner to resolve them.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"7f188921-8b7c-4646-b4d5-126c68b5a967">
<h3 local-id=3D"2145fc78-3d9b-40bb-ad04-585529be0f1b" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-1.2.1Step1-Expedite/On-Call(starthereeveryday)">1.2.1 Step 1 - Exped=
ite / On-Call (start here every day)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"8724afa5-8c96-4ac2-aa30-ea169a9385a4">Expedite/On-Call is fo=
r the <strong>most important and urgent</strong> work (e.g., on-call incide=
nts, major incidents, urgent unplanned work). Items in this swimlane should=
 have an explicit plan to exit Expedite quickly.</p>
<h4 local-id=3D"75cb5372-496f-4477-88e7-5c642013c5a1" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-On-Callitems(mustenterapositiveimprovementloop)">On-Call items (must=
 enter a positive improvement loop)</h4>
<p local-id=3D"6322d3be-7458-4b30-9e4c-c0f5a3fd3128">On-call incidents <str=
ong>must remain in the Expedite/On-Call swimlane</strong> until the team ha=
s agreed a plan of action to reduce re-occurrence. The stand-up outcome mus=
t include a concrete improvement action, for example:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"82da3ce5-719c-475f-b035-8c39ba10de74">
<li local-id=3D"db20605d81cc">
<p local-id=3D"5df41e85b266">A new backlog item to address root cause / tec=
h debt, or</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3b3d2e680650">
<p local-id=3D"b27020fba909">A Service Improvement Plan (SIP) item (e.g., c=
reating a Dynatrace alert or improving observability).</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"24f4fc7c-7297-444a-bc1a-3d27421983d9" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-OtherExpedite(nonon-callexpedite)">Other Expedite (non on-call exped=
ite)</h4>
<p local-id=3D"5bced19d-b212-4499-8115-f09719c32793">Non on-call expedite i=
tems are urgent/critical unplanned work (e.g., Major Incidents or urgent op=
erational work). These items should <strong>not sit in Expedite for long</s=
trong> (typically only a few days) and must leave stand-up with a clear pla=
n to resolve them <strong>ASAP</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"c2dc50fb-0e29-4925-882a-d82c26aa369f">Important notes for ho=
w this lane is used:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"a4c011be-b946-40d9-ac22-5f9c0fd598ca">
<li local-id=3D"061940339575">
<p local-id=3D"51c2c582a61a">This lane is sometimes used as an update mecha=
nism only (e.g., to provide visibility post=E2=80=93Major Incident resoluti=
on). If an item is in Expedite purely for updates, make sure there is still=
 clarity on its next action and where it belongs next.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"15b498386bb4">
<p local-id=3D"7d31e681777f">If the item is no longer as urgent as it was w=
hen first placed in Expedite, but still needs visibility and active follow-=
up, move it to Tracked (and add the appropriate reason/notes) rather than l=
eaving it in Expedite.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0c1eceed070b">
<p local-id=3D"24ab9643e060">If there=E2=80=99s a clear way to move it to T=
racked, do so =E2=80=94 especially when it has become =E2=80=9Cimportant bu=
t not immediate=E2=80=9D and benefits from being discussed until it=E2=80=
=99s unblocked or progressed.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"080b5fbb-63b2-4fc7-9c6f-98d342f03567">Expedite items are the=
 most important items on the board and it is the <strong>entire team=E2=80=
=99s responsibility</strong> to get them out of Expedite as soon as practic=
al.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"743dc3a2-5f46-4a68-a083-90334d48e1a2">
<h3 local-id=3D"47ae3a8d-429a-4bba-a3d3-ce92673ea6ee" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-1.2.2Step2-Reminder:ReviewFixedDeliveryworkitems(LastResponsibleMome=
nt/CoS:FixedDate)">1.2.2 Step 2 - Reminder: Review Fixed Delivery work item=
s (Last Responsible Moment / CoS: Fixed Date)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"9accbc9c-fc82-418f-a451-c01ad15fc700">Early in the stand-up,=
 the Board Driver performs the <strong>Last Responsible Moment (LRM)</stron=
g> check:</p>
<p local-id=3D"dcccd2f82904"></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"d4159d72-e0c2-4249-bc7d-7e8a6dbde8e4">
<li local-id=3D"e110da70d3db">
<p local-id=3D"70212815ff3f">Use the ADO search field to filter on <code>fi=
xed</code>.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d4ea64d125a2">
<p local-id=3D"1976b5d1935e">Review the prioritised backlog swimlanes (Plat=
forms, DBA, and S&amp;B).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"49fc0d7460d9">
<p local-id=3D"485e52f07698">Any item with <strong>Class of Service (CoS) =
=3D Fixed Date</strong> and a <strong>Start Date of =E2=80=9Ctoday=E2=80=9D=
</strong> must be assigned an owner.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"6acd39b4cda1">We assign a CoS of <strong>Fixed</strong> when=
 an item needs an LRM date =E2=80=94 the last moment we must start/pick up =
the work to deliver by a particular date:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6022208e0dde">
<li local-id=3D"622dcfedf732">
<p local-id=3D"1bfad183d9bc"><a class=3D"external-link" data-card-appearanc=
e=3D"inline" href=3D"https://blog.codinghorror.com/the-last-responsible-mom=
ent/" local-id=3D"17e517ce92cc" rel=3D"nofollow">https://blog.codinghorror.=
com/the-last-responsible-moment/</a></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"b45c6f39effc">There is a reminder card on the board to promp=
t the Board Driver to do this step early in the stand-up.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"f516595768f9">
<h3 local-id=3D"2733cf5fc3ea" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-1.2.3Step3-Remind=
er:ReviewStyleRules(CardColourRules)">1.2.3 Step 3 - Reminder: Review Style=
 Rules (Card Colour Rules)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"fbd8ec069b6c">Next, the Board Driver reviews any cards flagg=
ed by <strong>style rules</strong>. Style rules are intended to gently remi=
nd board users of the agreed rules (primarily WIP limit breakage and correc=
t swimlane placement).</p>
<p local-id=3D"3cff11064077">Rules of engagement:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"bec2d40ca403">
<li local-id=3D"ea2a568920d0">
<p local-id=3D"d2c57287b0ee"><strong>All cards flagged by style rules must =
be dealt with live during stand-up.</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4ef53c7bf8ed">
<p local-id=3D"ab9e4e9b19a7">Team members should ideally resolve style rule=
 breaks <strong>before</strong> stand-up so that stand-up remains focused o=
n Expedite &amp; Tracked.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"784ed7b75c46">
<p local-id=3D"9d9f4272b999">If someone is unsure how to resolve a style ru=
le break, it=E2=80=99s acceptable to handle it during stand-up.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"cfe800cb9fa5">Refer to <a data-card-appearance=3D"inline" hr=
ef=3D"https://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ECOT/pages/84895663=
20/Azure+DevOps+Board+ADO#3.5---Card-Colour-Rules-(Styling-Rules)-%E2%80%94=
-What-They-Mean-and-What-To-Do" local-id=3D"f52534e4aa91" rel=3D"nofollow">=
https://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ECOT/pages/8489566320/Azu=
re+DevOps+Board+ADO#3.5---Card-Colour-Rules-(Styling-Rules)-%E2%80%94-What-=
They-Mean-and-What-To-Do</a> section for meanings and fixes.</p>
<p local-id=3D"0535b47d0907">There is a reminder ticket on the board to pro=
mpt the Board Driver to run this step.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"a79adb0edda5">
<h3 local-id=3D"13b55c98dce4" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-1.2.4Step4-Tracke=
d(Blockedwork)">1.2.4 Step 4 - Tracked (Blocked work)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"78cd28d1ed72">After Expedite and the two reminders, the team=
 discusses <strong>Tracked</strong> items (blocked work).</p>
<p local-id=3D"141754fe962a">Why this matters:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"e604d938a26a">
<li local-id=3D"653c6d6963dc">
<p local-id=3D"abf3a23c07bd">Blocked work is expensive: make it visible to =
provoke conversation and action.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2dd7e76e6658">
<p local-id=3D"ff93bd897298">The Board Driver=E2=80=99s responsibility (and=
 everyone else=E2=80=99s) is to <strong>swarm</strong> blocked work items a=
nd help unblock them.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7fa8d75b0bc8">
<p local-id=3D"3532b0ca68b9">Tracked items should be uncomfortable to discu=
ss every day =E2=80=94 this is intentional and highlights when we=E2=80=99r=
e not unblocking quickly enough.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c03461c01687">Discussion guidance (keep it moving):</p>
<ul local-id=3D"58971788bf4f">
<li local-id=3D"757efccd18d8">
<p local-id=3D"6fa59efeb363">Some technical discussion is often necessary t=
o understand the block, but there should not be a lengthy or involved back-=
and-forth in stand-up.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"827fb584cebd">
<p local-id=3D"22df5aa3adea">Decide early if the item needs an <strong>offl=
ine/scheduled call</strong> with a subset of the team to progress it (and c=
apture who/when).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6b094050a150">
<p local-id=3D"64e2320d94c0">Anyone can call <strong>E.L.M.O.</strong> (=E2=
=80=9CEnough, Let=E2=80=99s Move On=E2=80=9D) at any time to keep stand-up =
on track and move detailed discussion offline:<a class=3D"external-link" da=
ta-card-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://medium.com/no-more-cargo-cult=
-agile/how-elmo-can-we-useful-for-you-and-your-team-89ed3aad82be" local-id=
=3D"b3f18a0411a5" rel=3D"nofollow">https://medium.com/no-more-cargo-cult-ag=
ile/how-elmo-can-we-useful-for-you-and-your-team-89ed3aad82be</a></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"43a51fafba97">The key question for each Tracked item:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b8b4246a8fe6">
<li local-id=3D"b1f1c25a95d7">
<p local-id=3D"b54ee719ff45"><strong>What needs to happen to get this work =
item out of Tracked ASAP?</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"77e5509e1b81">Additional guidance:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"ff548f86-ba10-4bbb-9e01-84768a40bbfa">
<li local-id=3D"3ac2ce0f-d07e-4371-b23e-747b825605de">
<p local-id=3D"40ab550c0f84">Ensure <strong>all blocked cards have the =E2=
=80=9Cblocked details=E2=80=9D filled out</strong>. This should clearly des=
cribe what is preventing progress and <em>what specific action or input</em=
> would resolve it.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ce00b242-6d93-47cb-ba1d-21b04d7d77c9">
<p local-id=3D"d3977ea7d931"><strong>Tracked is only for items that must be=
 discussed every day in stand=E2=80=91up</strong> until the block is remove=
d.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"aa578e76-5e01-4e14-b65e-b7ebe2a4c1a0">
<p local-id=3D"e7ba9fe9ba59">If the item is simply <strong>waiting for a me=
eting, decision, or scheduled event</strong>, and does <em>not</em> require=
 daily discussion, <strong>use Parked instead</strong> =E2=80=94 Parked ite=
ms are reviewed only at the appropriate cadence, not daily.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"7c6aecb6fa28">
<h3 local-id=3D"3fefb68206be" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-1.2.5Step5-Close-=
out(quickhygienecheck)">1.2.5 Step 5 - Close-out (quick hygiene check)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"49a45e9c2236">Before ending stand-up:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"e9b366ede510">
<li local-id=3D"c1a2d58d4415">
<p local-id=3D"8c0ee07d3092">Confirm any changes agreed during stand-up are=
 reflected on the board (owner updates, swimlane moves, blocked reasons).</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3f1078245654">
<p local-id=3D"c7108c774355">Ensure any new follow-up work (prevention acti=
ons, SIPs, backlog items) has an owner and a clear next step.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"46d3eed05d53">
<h3 local-id=3D"749397145a01" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-1.2.6Parked(oncea=
month)">1.2.6 Parked (once a month)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"4b4c7becb090">Parked holds long-term Tracked items that are =
paused or blocked and don=E2=80=99t need daily DSU airtime.</p>
<p local-id=3D"d6b1ca0a9245"><strong>Not a dumping ground</strong>:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"1e3c98967a25">
<li local-id=3D"7f436d2ad5c0">
<p local-id=3D"e2f87a0b8309">Parked items always have a named owner.</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"1b47a6ff195e">
<p local-id=3D"f627ce89e11a">Owners keep items up to date between monthly r=
eviews (reason, notes, and what must change to unpark).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5bd7dece92e7">
<p local-id=3D"2581efe4a906">If circumstances change (new info, dependency =
resolves, priority shifts), update and move it out of Parked (usually back =
to Tracked).</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"8d5d226361cb"><strong>Review cadence</strong>:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6262da703111">
<li local-id=3D"b184f9cecc01">
<p local-id=3D"5cd8f44b7fe2">Review monthly.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ce195c5428d7">
<p local-id=3D"a41425bc2ff4">Each monthly review results in one of: keep pa=
rked, move to Tracked, pull into Breakdown/Implement, or close/remove.</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"463b7f7a8653"><strong>Blocked Details:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"2735b1c4b356">Even though Parked items don=E2=80=99t appear =
in daily stand=E2=80=91ups, <strong>they still require =E2=80=9Cblocked det=
ails=E2=80=9D</strong> to describe:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"f2723661-0792-4829-a90a-f94ed3694b81">
<li local-id=3D"dd114bfd-28bc-4c60-8cc4-da5acbe64b96">
<p local-id=3D"a85190307763">what is currently preventing progress, and</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"b2fa1a25-4c77-4f2d-b40e-9dc0af5b061b">
<p local-id=3D"2ee2494f4d38">what action/input/event is needed to move the =
item forward.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"378695dc29c0">This ensures that long=E2=80=91term blocks rem=
ain visible and actionable, rather than being forgotten.</p>
<h1 local-id=3D"fdd47678-b676-419d-80c6-9cc5cfbf2869" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-2.Configuringtheboardforthefirsttime">2. Configuring the board for t=
he first time</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"b2c0d52f-b826-4126-9eec-83b8cb2a3325" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-2.1EnablingUKtimedisplayformat">2.1 Enabling UK time display format<=
/h2>
<p local-id=3D"6171cef2-774c-4df3-87e1-179eb95cea19">By default, Azure Boar=
d displays date/time in US format</p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-fil=
e-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D=
"confluence-embedded-image image-left" alt=3D"image-20260116-132720.png" wi=
dth=3D"205" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"87c4b9404acff268467b836a04054db712a1d8c=
f99a948f7cee029de58f2fea3" data-image-src=3D"https://emishealthgroup.atlass=
