<h1 local-id=3D"43accb72-0196-40d9-b138-0a4bee9b843c" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-3.UsingtheAzureDevOpsBoard-Terminologyexplained">3. Using the Azure =
DevOps Board - Terminology explained</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"d6b1d555-ee4b-4b3a-9dfe-365b098bc541" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-3.1-SwimLanes">3.1 - Swim Lanes</h2>
<p local-id=3D"6671f27a-28de-47b6-9800-66a084530174">The swim lanes run hor=
izontally across the board and are used to help organise the work.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"55001297-a100-4689-bba0-19d3250bd4fa" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-3.1.1-Expedite/On-Call">3.1.1 - Expedite / On-Call</h3>
<p local-id=3D"4cd5fb02-2e91-4e05-9165-61ab246f9910">This swim lane is used=
 for Major Incidents, on call and anything which comes in as business criti=
cal and has to be done immediately.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p local-id=3D"845e155c-abe8-4fa0-a0fd-a423bef220a4"><strong>INFORMATION -<=
/strong> Major Incidents and on call work items should remain in this swim =
lane (under Validate) until they have been discussed on the Daily Stand Up =
(DSU) Call the following day.</p>
<p local-id=3D"11e17f47ad0e">Items in this lane are treated as the <strong>=
most urgent work</strong> and should have a clear plan to exit Expedite qui=
ckly.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"9c04ffd6-88c7-4f13-963a-ea8087239072" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-3.1.2-Tracked">3.1.2 - Tracked</h3>
<p local-id=3D"9bc45ca4-e559-41d5-abb4-d20033ef964b">This swim lane is used=
 for work which cannot be progressed as it is blocked by an internal or ext=
ernal factor. Any tickets which are blocked should be marked as blocked by =
placing in this lane and entering a 'Blocked Reason'.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p local-id=3D"23274cfa-1d30-4e8b-b585-783f6514b8a4"><strong>INFORMATION</s=
trong> - Tracked work items should be discussed on the Daily Stand Up (DSU)=
 Call until they become unblocked.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"3cc7cc2a-1a87-4a9f-bc20-954d8ca1b4bb" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-3.1.3-Work">3.1.3 - Work</h3>
<p local-id=3D"83435f0f-c3e9-44d6-9fde-f4866bc56f0b">This swim lane is used=
 for work which is on going and does not need to be discussed. It should ju=
st be happening.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"cf4aff82-6736-4dfb-9339-808a413492aa" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-3.1.4-Parked">3.1.4 - Parked</h3>
<p local-id=3D"bf58aeba-c7eb-47f1-b458-1f7e2bb08c96">This swim lane is used=
 for work which is parked for an extended period of time, this is not the s=
ame as the =E2=80=9CTracked=E2=80=9D swim lane.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"cba9df27-5698-41cc-b075-e402a0e802b1" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-3.1.5-ScheduledChanges">3.1.5 - Scheduled Changes</h3>
<p local-id=3D"515fdf88-14a2-4302-8a5a-1f02ef1afd92">This swim lane is used=
 for work which has a scheduled change logged against it and is awaiting co=
mpletion. For example changes which are adhering to the 48 hour change impl=
ementation rule.</p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p local-id=3D"9978c3da6d93">You must enter the ServiceNow CHG reference in=
 the 'SN CHG ID' field.</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"3a450c515ce2" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.1.6-Ready(Prior=
itised)Backlog(persub-team)">3.1.6 - Ready (Prioritised) Backlog (per sub-t=
eam)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"55579b093a30">The <strong>Ready (Prioritised) Backlog</stron=
g> swim lanes are the team-owned, prioritised queues of work that have been=
 <strong>scored</strong> and are <strong>eligible to be pulled</strong> whe=
n capacity exists.</p>
<p local-id=3D"0ad3e2b2eea3">Ready Backlog swim lanes:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"07f223067b53">
<li local-id=3D"d63f8d77ffc4">
<p local-id=3D"0f354f0e0e68"><strong>Platform Ready Backlog</strong></p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"4b7bd9793655">
<p local-id=3D"38dc66317a52"><strong>DBA Ready Backlog</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"58112017dd7d">
<p local-id=3D"2b14b305bf4d"><strong>S&amp;B Ready Backlog</strong></p></li=
>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"2f461838a5b9"><strong>Purpose</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"20e7669f105c">
<li local-id=3D"461e64449f1b">
<p local-id=3D"cec255490eb5">Holds work that has completed replenishment sc=
oring (WSJF) and is now ordered by priority.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7d0ca84083ad">
<p local-id=3D"62910664d1ea">Acts as the =E2=80=9Cnext-up=E2=80=9D queue th=
e team pulls from, supporting a pull system (finish work before starting mo=
re).</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"933c58b04252"><strong>Rules</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"acdefe84beac">
<li local-id=3D"5ca44cd5c278">
<p local-id=3D"7c2d5f03134f">Items in a Ready Backlog are ordered by <a cla=
ss=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://productschool.com/blog/product-fundame=
ntals/wsjf-agile" rel=3D"nofollow"><strong>WSJF score</strong></a> (highest=
 first)</p>
<ul local-id=3D"469fca781431">
<li local-id=3D"346e57530bde">
<p local-id=3D"438498d1f26e">except where overridden by Class of Service: E=
xpedite, see <a data-card-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://emishealthg=
roup.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ECOT/pages/8489566320/Azure+DevOps+Board+ADO=
#(CoS)%3A-Expedite-(Ready-Backlog-override)" local-id=3D"f97580ac38ab" rel=
=3D"nofollow">https://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ECOT/pages/=
8489566320/Azure+DevOps+Board+ADO#(CoS)%3A-Expedite-(Ready-Backlog-override=
)</a></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"8f45e798276a">
<p local-id=3D"3f35669b9f58">Work is pulled from Ready Backlog into active =
flow only when there is available capacity (WIP).</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"7658dccd1150" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.1.7=E2=80=93Unp=
rioritisedBacklog(persub-team)">3.1.7 =E2=80=93 Unprioritised Backlog (per =
sub-team)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"a3c6f643debe">The <strong>Unprioritised Backlog</strong> swi=
m lanes are the intake queues for planned work that has <strong>not yet bee=
n scored/prioritised</strong>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"1b9811ade362">Unprioritised Backlog swim lanes:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"2bf6e7ce9b30">
<li local-id=3D"a7b5e2be62ba">
<p local-id=3D"f5793945c685"><strong>Platform Unprioritised Backlog</strong=
></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"555269ec100f">
<p local-id=3D"ce331b64f3f5"><strong>DBA Unprioritised Backlog</strong></p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"328835d3603f">
<p local-id=3D"a60398e0cdf3"><strong>S&amp;B Unprioritised Backlog</strong>=
</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"81e162612df4"><strong>Purpose</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"f25af3a54b10">
<li local-id=3D"a6b85e0eca69">
<p local-id=3D"2f77beb041de">Captures new work requests so they are visible=
 and don=E2=80=99t get lost, without prematurely forcing an order.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d8a398016c87">
<p local-id=3D"f003138827bd">Separates =E2=80=9Ccaptured=E2=80=9D work from=
 =E2=80=9Cready to pull=E2=80=9D work.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"fe609e861704"><strong>Rule</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"23a63ad9da5a">
<li local-id=3D"ccb96c1cd406">
<p local-id=3D"5a37e16b421b">All work that is <strong>not urgent</strong> (=
and not treated as immediate KTLO) goes into the relevant team=E2=80=99s Un=
prioritised Backlog first, to be scored during replenishment.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"9ff88cf083db" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.1.8=E2=80=93Rep=
lenishmentprocess(WSJFscoring=E2=86=92ReadyBacklog)">3.1.8 =E2=80=93 Replen=
ishment process (WSJF scoring =E2=86=92 Ready Backlog)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"72ccdbc6cf09"><strong>Cadence</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"6b234043b702">
<li local-id=3D"7f2c03e8c77e">
<p local-id=3D"0c3d5e9b57c5">Replenishment is performed in the daily <stron=
g>Replenishment</strong> meeting.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"1b3b69e900fc"><strong>Process</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"8cca63d10c01">
<li local-id=3D"4087e8a1ac02">
<p local-id=3D"3c41b8bb06f2"><strong>Capture:</strong> New planned work goe=
s into the correct team=E2=80=99s <strong>Unprioritised Backlog</strong>.</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"abc8ec07b5d2">
<p local-id=3D"1971dd4fe9c3"><strong>Score:</strong> During replenishment, =
the team assigns a <strong>WSJF score</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8fa4962294bb">
<p local-id=3D"a031b42bfc89"><strong>Promote:</strong> Once scored, the ite=
m moves to that team=E2=80=99s <strong>Ready Backlog</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"841d09bf412d">
<p local-id=3D"e4c12af01865"><strong>Order:</strong> Items in Ready Backlog=
 are ordered by WSJF (highest =E2=86=92 lowest).</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"741d3d993002"><strong>WSJF (Weighted Shortest Job First) =E2=
=80=93 summary</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"410c3ded1c74">
<li local-id=3D"df0b8a3b250a">
<p local-id=3D"da0fb432afc0">WSJF helps decide what to do next by balancing=
 <strong>Cost of Delay</strong> against <strong>Job Size (Effort)</strong>.=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a4c834b4573b">
<p local-id=3D"a971564e2d24">Cost of Delay considers <strong>Urgency</stron=
g>, <strong>Value</strong>, and <strong>Risk/Opportunity</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"92f953392cb2" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.1.9=E2=80=93Cla=
ssofService">3.1.9 =E2=80=93 Class of Service</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"center" data-local-id=3D"0b7=
0b9de6f1f" data-table-display-mode=3D"default" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 154.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 605.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d00d5d742273">
<th data-highlight-colour=3D"#f4f5f7" data-local-id=3D"8c6acd362ff7" class=
=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"539d56384432"><strong>Class of Service</strong></p></th>
<th data-highlight-colour=3D"#f4f5f7" data-local-id=3D"a62e181a11e7" class=
=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"d8a8b5842ee3"><strong>Policy &amp; How to Handle It</strong>=
</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"a214eefc5eeb">
<td data-local-id=3D"2b202ecedff9" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ff3dca0c83ad">Expedite</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a80231775cb0" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3452ea367eda">For time-sensitive work that should be done ne=
xt, but is <strong>not an incident</strong> and does <strong>not</strong> b=
elong in the <strong>Expedite / On-Call</strong> swim lane.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"a54eb017cb3d">
<td data-local-id=3D"42b1b925b124" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0bcca865f032">Fixed Date</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a74077e279fd" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"886f3547f056"><strong>Pull at the "last responsible moment":=
</strong> This work must be completed by a specific date. The team pulls it=
 ahead of other work to ensure the deadline is met.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"cb3beddbebc1">
<td data-local-id=3D"4c12cfc75219" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0889c338d213">Standard</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"5bacce682fba" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d5f0ef65b8d4"><strong>Pull based on WSJF score:</strong> Thi=
s is the default class for most planned work. When a team member has capaci=
ty, they pull the Standard item with the highest WSJF score.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"43b4a4fb089c">
<td data-local-id=3D"1959c60359e7" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b30beb0c8e7f">Intangible</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"91d02d63fea8" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"aa7f6dc9849d"><strong>Pull when the dedicated slot is free:<=
/strong> This is for important but not urgent work.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 local-id=3D"a9c33055a8ef" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-(CoS):Expedite(Re=
adyBacklogoverride)">(CoS): Expedite (Ready Backlog override)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"dc64f2599a26">In addition to WSJF-based prioritisation, we u=
se <strong>CoS =3D Expedite</strong> for items that are urgent and time-sen=
sitive, but <strong>not critical enough</strong> to belong in the <strong>E=
xpedite / On-Call</strong> swim lane (i.e., not a Major Incident or immedia=
te service-impacting emergency).</p>
<p local-id=3D"2528393814c8"><strong>How it works</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"fcea3dfe9698">
<li local-id=3D"c9443ea677c2">
<p local-id=3D"769c74ba172c">If an item is marked <strong>CoS =3D Expedite<=
/strong>, it may be placed at the <strong>top of the relevant team=E2=80=99=
s Ready Backlog regardless of WSJF score</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6984a0ad56d2">
<p local-id=3D"3e586a008339">Ready Backlog remains WSJF-ordered for standar=
d work; CoS Expedite is an explicit priority override.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"9f750f23c123"><strong>Distinction</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"0df5993f2d7b">
<li local-id=3D"36d541333c77">
<p local-id=3D"a916fedfbc98"><strong>Expedite / On-Call swim lane:</strong>=
 Major Incidents / on-call / business critical items handled immediately an=
d retained for DSU visibility.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"acf7999b61cc">
<p local-id=3D"0601e7cc092c"><strong>CoS Expedite (Ready Backlog):</strong>=
 urgent planned work that should be done next, without treating it as incid=
ent/on-call work.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"335d35fe8d71"><strong>Usage guidance</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"3b99b75bba86">
<li local-id=3D"f545d0291488">
<p local-id=3D"ace53d95e79f">Use CoS Expedite sparingly to avoid underminin=
g WSJF and creating a permanent =E2=80=9Curgent queue=E2=80=9D.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d6c9355dc52d">
<p local-id=3D"ccb0f8529433">Confirm during replenishment: why it is Expedi=
te, that it doesn=E2=80=99t belong in Expedite/On-Call, and what the next p=
ull action is when capacity exists.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"9e43dcde-0596-4d69-a057-6da276196e36" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-3.2-PullCriteriaakaDefinitionofDone">3.2 - Pull Criteria aka Definit=
ion of Done</h2>
<p local-id=3D"3cdd6641-d1aa-4b08-8858-1a19c5f4d1bd">The pull criteria are =
defined on the board above each Step column and describe the rules which sh=
ould always be followed before moving a Work Item from one Step to the next=
 (For example moving between 'Breakdown - doing' and 'Breakdown - done').</=
p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
<p local-id=3D"6dba5cf4-bd0f-4ea3-9cb2-d7d5b0143620"><strong>INFORMATION</s=
trong> - It is important to adhere to the agreed =E2=80=98WIP=E2=80=99 limi=
ts specified in the Steps</p>
</div>
</div>
<p local-id=3D"a2f9d20c-e897-470c-945c-fbe9d48f05d1">&nbsp;The Pull Criteri=
a for each Step can be viewed by hovering over the <em>i</em> symbol above =
each Step</p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wra=
pper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-ima=
ge image-left" alt=3D"image-20260116-145757.png" width=3D"428" loading=3D"l=
azy" src=3D"245b0a25a7b3a7023e6cb203c419326355cfa1819a8a5b1d2aca8f08a0d1d35=
2" data-image-src=3D"https://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki/download/at=
tachments/8489566320/image-20260116-145757.png?version=3D1&amp;modification=
Date=3D1768575481445&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"196"=
 data-width=3D"428" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resourc=
e-id=3D"8491401236" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource=
-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image-20260116-1=
45757.png" data-base-url=3D"https://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki" dat=
a-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container=
-id=3D"8489566320" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"31" data-media=
-id=3D"57a8bbb7-335e-4afc-878b-00f43aea0e2b" data-media-type=3D"file" heigh=
t=3D"196"></span>
<h2 local-id=3D"3f632821-eeea-4755-ae33-7d381ebf859d" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-3.3-FlowStateColumns">3.3 - Flow State Columns</h2>
<p local-id=3D"8baf2f15-2656-4980-9bdb-9f5e516e553d">The flow state columns=
 run vertically across the board and are used to define what state a work i=
tem is currently in.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"f97fd5a64fd1" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-PullCriteria(Defi=
nitionofDone)=E2=80=93howyoumovework">Pull Criteria (Definition of Done) =
=E2=80=93 how you move work</h3>
<p local-id=3D"2a5e3c331442">Each Step has =E2=80=9CPull Criteria=E2=80=9D =
(Definition of Done) that must be satisfied before a card can move forward.=
</p>
<h5 local-id=3D"cec717914e0b" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-Rulesofmovement">=
Rules of movement</h5>
<ul local-id=3D"5a955e8a0e3e">
<li local-id=3D"3ba1567fd714">
<p local-id=3D"04146219fd4c">Doing =E2=86=92 Done (within a Step): A card c=
an only be moved from [Doing] to [Done] when the Pull Criteria for that Ste=
p has been met.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f436b9c06e3a">
<p local-id=3D"6e0c6a203c9a">Done =E2=86=92 Next Step Doing: A card can onl=
y be pulled into the next Step=E2=80=99s [Doing] when:</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"37c1c3242cb5">&nbsp; =E2=80=93 the Pull Criteria for the pre=
vious Step has been met, AND</p>
<p local-id=3D"8d9d50775b7a">&nbsp; =E2=80=93 there is free WIP capacity in=
 the next Step.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"87b4f8505aa7">
<h3 local-id=3D"9b42d5b65271" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.3.1=E2=80=93Bre=
akdown[Doing]">3.3.1 =E2=80=93 Breakdown [Doing]</h3>
<p local-id=3D"177cda5f2d73"></p>
<p local-id=3D"d60f43616ea2">Work items which are being broken down should =
be in this column. The Pull Criteria under the Breakdown column should be f=
ollowed in order to move the work item into the =E2=80=98Breakdown [Done]=
=E2=80=99 step.</p>
<p local-id=3D"9ff0f5bad5cc">Breakdown Pull Criteria (to move Breakdown [Do=
ing] =E2=86=92 Breakdown [Done]):</p>
<ul local-id=3D"1141f7156a76">
<li local-id=3D"f855ec3d320b">
<p local-id=3D"b4d9b7b3cb72">Needs to be assigned</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"534aa2861662">
<p local-id=3D"bc305933ad06">Area Path must be assigned to the correct sub-=
team</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"74ac57c130fc">
<p local-id=3D"0efa067602c1">Assigned a Source</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2d40a747e285">
<p local-id=3D"077ba9ea4d94">Broken down into a piece of work sized to: =E2=
=80=9CMinimum 30 minutes =E2=80=93 Max 3 days-ish=E2=80=9D</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f0d267bc1bf5">
<p local-id=3D"36df3c1fe5e9">Breakdown sizing guidance: <a data-card-appear=
ance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/E=
COT/pages/8489566320/Azure+DevOps+Board+ADO#Size-cards-using-the-Breakdown-=
%5BDoing%5D-definition" local-id=3D"b3423dae0a0f" rel=3D"nofollow">https://=
emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ECOT/pages/8489566320/Azure+DevOp=
s+Board+ADO#Size-cards-using-the-Breakdown-%5BDoing%5D-definition</a></p></=
li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"63b58bb9c14d"></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"bc3432a122fd" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.3.2=E2=80=93Bre=
akdown[Done]">3.3.2 =E2=80=93 Breakdown [Done]</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ed52c90e4cc8"></p>
<p local-id=3D"d1764eef4e1d">Work items which are fully broken down and rea=
dy to move into the =E2=80=98Implement [Doing]=E2=80=99 column should be in=
 this column. Work items can only be moved into =E2=80=98Implement [Doing]=
=E2=80=99 if there=E2=80=99s free WIP.</p>
<p local-id=3D"365cf60870db"></p>
<p local-id=3D"83c01d5bc368">(Mechanism reminder: You can only pull a card =
into Implement [Doing] when there is free WIP in Implement.)</p>
<hr local-id=3D"10ea29939223">
<h3 local-id=3D"fbe3895dfdc3" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.3.3=E2=80=93Imp=
lement[Doing]">3.3.3 =E2=80=93 Implement [Doing]</h3>
<p local-id=3D"c6020be9d95c"></p>
<p local-id=3D"b62742fbaf3c">Work items which are being worked on should be=
 in this column. The Pull Criteria under the Implement column should be fol=
lowed in order to move the work item into the =E2=80=98Implement [Done]=E2=
=80=99 step.</p>
<p local-id=3D"3bff72647236"></p>
<p local-id=3D"7ea37a79167c">Implement Pull Criteria (to move Implement [Do=
ing] =E2=86=92 Implement [Done]):</p>
<ul local-id=3D"81cae9848856">
<li local-id=3D"9721911fe7f9">
<p local-id=3D"1ba6eb39ce17">Tech Debt, Strategy and Continuous Improvement=
:</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"a988486483a6">&nbsp; =E2=80=93 Raise PR</p>
<p local-id=3D"54f796bcb04b">&nbsp; =E2=80=93 Review PR</p>
<p local-id=3D"6d8cdb4598e1">&nbsp; =E2=80=93 Test PR</p>
<ul local-id=3D"222624387dc3">
<li local-id=3D"ad2ab7fa53a8">
<p local-id=3D"97938933a1d2">Raise a change and place the card in the Sched=
uled Changes swimlane if lead time is required</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c81a8dcd41cf">&nbsp; =E2=80=93 Must have a CHG number in the=
 =E2=80=9CSN Ref.=E2=80=9D field</p>
<ul local-id=3D"c886874a1c5d">
<li local-id=3D"0ff474c8313f">
<p local-id=3D"3e16253717ad">Do the work</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"b43e3d5c5306"></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"dafe60378fa9" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.3.4=E2=80=93Imp=
lement[Done]">3.3.4 =E2=80=93 Implement [Done]</h3>
<p local-id=3D"38e76a4b7598"></p>
<p local-id=3D"d42fe26d02f0">Work items that have been completed should be =
placed under this column. Work items can only be moved into =E2=80=98Valida=
te=E2=80=99 if there=E2=80=99s free WIP.</p>
<p local-id=3D"7d51a835446b"></p>
<p local-id=3D"37644a5fcf00">(Mechanism reminder: You can only pull a card =
into Validate when there is free WIP in Validate.)</p>
<hr local-id=3D"fc45e5f2fe3b">
<h3 local-id=3D"5d13ff7df449" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.3.5=E2=80=93Val=
idate">3.3.5 =E2=80=93 Validate</h3>
<p local-id=3D"5800c4aaa0cb"></p>
<p local-id=3D"4930ac9d0c16">Work items which are being validated as succes=
sful should be in this column.</p>
<p local-id=3D"a027fa31fb68"></p>
<p local-id=3D"f9e49751f7c2">Validate is a special case:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"72e38c2b5ef2">
<li local-id=3D"faeb49494556">
<p local-id=3D"d9dd589b0217">Validate is a single column (no [Doing]/[Done]=
).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8e748ff77b91">
<p local-id=3D"0839c0557509">When validation is complete and the criteria a=
re met, the card moves to the final Done column.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"d236c957a84f"></p>
<p local-id=3D"c1194b394bd9">Validate Pull Criteria (to move Validate =E2=
=86=92 Done):</p>
<ul local-id=3D"5fd41c91bbd0">
<li local-id=3D"6984cfae2cb8">
<p local-id=3D"4bfabe2e6bfc">Tech Debt, Strategy and Continuous Improvement=
:</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"3d5297290b92">&nbsp; =E2=80=93 Deployed to Production and no=
 issues</p>
<ul local-id=3D"ae6bf7d4d314">
<li local-id=3D"0d78a9690b89">
<p local-id=3D"b735a1dd49f5">EMISNow RITM:</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"183e6f1fe604">&nbsp; =E2=80=93 Confirm with requester that w=
ork is complete</p>
<hr local-id=3D"8d148b7fc743">
<h3 local-id=3D"b7a1da734444" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.3.6=E2=80=93Don=
e">3.3.6 =E2=80=93 Done</h3>
<p local-id=3D"434fd6d29630"></p>
<p local-id=3D"db558af5355d">Work items which are completed / done should b=
e in this column.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"9520725270cd">
<h3 local-id=3D"a00dcc66a8d5" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.3.7=E2=80=93Whe=
nPullCriteriaAreMetbutWIPIsFull">3.3.7 =E2=80=93 When Pull Criteria Are Met=
 but WIP Is Full</h3>
<p local-id=3D"f33f94b2-3023-4b4f-8dd7-706bb27740f7">When a card has met th=
e Pull Criteria for the next Step but there is no free WIP capacity in that=
 Step:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b9b6edfa-f0a3-4521-9921-237dbf99fa23">
<li local-id=3D"a1596bbf51df">
<p local-id=3D"0155cd033f2a">Treat it as a <strong>signal to focus on flow<=
/strong>, not to start more work.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9628c1af807f">
<p local-id=3D"db894944c8cf">Progress the items already in the next Step so=
 they free up capacity.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2a91f9b83e7e">
<p local-id=3D"4e8a8ded871d">If an item is stalled for days due to an exter=
nal dependency:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"053514e7273e">
<li local-id=3D"4aededbf3850">
<p local-id=3D"4f685a363958">Move it to <strong>Tracked</strong> (with a cl=
ear Blocked Reason) so it stays visible and discussed.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"4ced4c607d00">
<p local-id=3D"ed908d15d33d">If validation is complete and there=E2=80=99s =
nothing left to do, move it to Done.</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"61de74cc510c" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-WhatifthePullCrit=
eriahasbeenmetbutthere=E2=80=99snofreeWIPinthenextStep?">What if the Pull C=
riteria has been met but there=E2=80=99s no free WIP in the next Step?</h4>
<h4 local-id=3D"881458469142" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-Answer">Answer</h=
4>
<p local-id=3D"f28c0d6da004">This is a good thing and is meant to happen. I=
t indicates your WIP is full and you do not have capacity to take on additi=
onal work in that Step.</p>
<p local-id=3D"9df55fc1da83">What to do:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"648e7dd912a2">
<li local-id=3D"d9c9b928d317">
<p local-id=3D"8ed11fdf8f38">Treat it as a signal to focus on flow: progres=
s the items that are currently =E2=80=9Cblocking=E2=80=9D capacity in the n=
ext Step.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c176d7c0041f">
<p local-id=3D"a64f2b4ede40">Example: If you=E2=80=99re waiting in Validate=
 on feedback, chase the requester (use common sense).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f7d38f24e95c">
<p local-id=3D"81d3b6e4e05a">If an item is stalled for days due to an exter=
nal dependency, consider moving it to Tracked (External Dependency) so it r=
emains visible and actively discussed.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c72d1d401420">
<p local-id=3D"3c7e63a47675">If validation is complete and there=E2=80=99s =
nothing left to do, move it to Done.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"1d0ea5a7-c37a-46b4-88f1-fae90af2616a" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-3.4-WIPLimits">3.4 - WIP Limits</h2>
<p local-id=3D"32ba6b15-66ee-4572-bba3-9cd020ed90d0">The maximum no. of car=
ds/work items allowed in each column/step, per person. The limit prevents i=
ndividuals starting new work when already at full capacity.</p>
<p local-id=3D"e85fbdfc35ea">WIP limits cap how many items can be in a work=
flow stage at once so that people <strong>finish work before starting more<=
/strong>, <strong>reduce multitasking/context switching</strong>, and <stro=
ng>make bottlenecks visible</strong> when work starts to pile up.</p>
<p local-id=3D"fa7f2da7-4818-44ba-b5cc-25d1aa5448b7">Displayed on the right=
-hand side of the =E2=80=98/' at the top of each column/step (the no. on th=
e left-hand side can be ignored, it=E2=80=99s not possible to hide on Azure=
 board, but is irrelevant to our Kanban implementation)</p><span class=3D"c=
onfluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-ma=
nual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-center" alt=3D"ima=
ge-20240926-140415.png" width=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"93e0858784a91=
d4ccb112a78e0ee04cfc10ebd87011ec6e81f6fe281f0f17134" data-image-src=3D"http=
s://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/8489566320/imag=
e-20240926-140415.png?version=3D2&amp;modificationDate=3D1768579101607&amp;=
cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"38" data-width=3D"898" data-u=
nresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"8492023867" data-l=
inked-resource-version=3D"2" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-=
linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image-20240926-140415.png" data-base-url=
=3D"https://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-resource-conten=
t-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"8489566320" data-=
linked-resource-container-version=3D"31" data-media-id=3D"de4410d1-674f-43a=
c-9502-c49f10537fd9" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"19"></span>
<p local-id=3D"4e13553b-330a-4038-854d-73603f8e7815">&nbsp;</p>
<ul local-id=3D"a29673b9-9453-40c1-abec-db577abd9ab0">
<li local-id=3D"c978f252-fc57-4f7e-a4ff-f8b0f7210908">
<p local-id=3D"0be7c3de-7a88-4d9d-9a6d-01c6aaf1cf33">Breakdown - No more th=
an 2 cards</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ede62547-a848-4803-8f0c-ccde401805a3">
<p local-id=3D"ee93b2bf-53d2-49b2-9fe9-fdef4c3eb383">Implement - No more th=
an 2 cards</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"56a605c7-fe92-46b7-a8df-477e8fef015a">
<p local-id=3D"9673a729-12cb-4e26-b765-6a872e288327">Validate - No more tha=
n 2 cards</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bbbcc2ba-9d0f-48a7-8517-4167be977160">
<p local-id=3D"7ee2a173-44e3-4c4c-8f68-b1db816aefad">Any breaches of WIP -<=
/p>
<ul local-id=3D"49633c8d9990">
<li local-id=3D"46ab6605f53a">
<p local-id=3D"df9f5540284b">See full details: <a data-card-appearance=3D"i=
nline" href=3D"https://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/ECOT/pages=
/8489566320/Azure+DevOps+Board+ADO#WIP-Limit-Exceeded" local-id=3D"14c0cdf6=
d8f9" rel=3D"nofollow">https://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/EC=
OT/pages/8489566320/Azure+DevOps+Board+ADO#WIP-Limit-Exceeded</a></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"169425b2-3644-4f14-8fce-5db34209a28d">
<p local-id=3D"c38858aa257d">Don=E2=80=99t start/pull anything new into thi=
s step while it=E2=80=99s over the limit.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"12a66d6b-076c-4628-a1a6-7f40daf31101">
<p local-id=3D"95d7fcab3a42">Finish or move one of the in-progress items fo=
rward so the count drops to WIP Limit threshold.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2013ad07-4fd2-46dc-ab65-775cbe74e40b">
<p local-id=3D"406719ac0bfc">If you must reduce WIP quickly, move the lowes=
t-priority item(s) to Tracked until the limit is met.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"2e366aa0-e2b3-4bae-8932-c4f435f082c2" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoar=
d(ADO)-3.5-CardColourRules(StylingRules)=E2=80=94WhatTheyMeanandWhatToDo">3=
.5 - Card Colour Rules (Styling Rules) =E2=80=94 What They Mean and What To=
 Do</h2>
<p local-id=3D"3fd88cbb-1550-4729-86ec-6b7c337fbf1f">Azure DevOps Boards us=
es <strong>card styling rules</strong> to make important exceptions stand o=
ut. If you notice a card <strong>change colour</strong>, it=E2=80=99s a vis=
ual warning that <strong>something isn=E2=80=99t right</strong>=E2=80=94the=
 work item has matched a rule that flags a missing step, incorrect placemen=
t, or incomplete information.</p>
<p local-id=3D"6374b9a0-dff1-4c3e-ba24-0d360e2498f9">In other words: <stron=
g>there=E2=80=99s a process rule you=E2=80=99re expected to follow, and the=
 card colour indicates you haven=E2=80=99t met it yet</strong>. Treat colou=
red cards as prompts to quickly triage the item, apply the required update =
(for example, assign an owner, set the right Area Path, add a blocked reaso=
n, or move it into the correct swimlane), and return the card to a =E2=80=
=9Chealthy=E2=80=9D state</p>
<p local-id=3D"409c895543d8"></p>
<h3 local-id=3D"f217cfccef84" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-HowtheTag-BasedHi=
ghlightSystemWorks">How the Tag-Based Highlight System Works</h3>
<p local-id=3D"405bf53bb357"></p>
<p local-id=3D"7da1aa77f961">Some styling rules are driven automatically by=
 a board hygiene process that runs on a schedule. This process applies two =
tags together to flag a work item:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"58f5840eca8a">
<li local-id=3D"1f983f3e91af">
<p local-id=3D"c10826e8edb7">NEEDS-ATTENTION =E2=80=94 the trigger tag. The=
 board style rule fires on this single tag, keeping the rule simple and con=
sistent regardless of what the underlying problem is.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0cfbed3add3a">
<p local-id=3D"38a4eceef5e9">FIX:&lt;reason&gt; =E2=80=94 the reason tag. T=
his explains what specific rule has been breached (e.g., FIX:WIP-Limit, FIX=
:Expedite-Age). Multiple FIX tags can exist on the same item if it has more=
 than one violation.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"addda163fd32">To clear a tag-based highlight, resolve the un=
derlying issue (see the relevant rule below). The automated process will re=
move the tags on its next scheduled run once the issue is no longer detecte=
d. Do not manually remove NEEDS-ATTENTION or FIX tags =E2=80=94 they will s=
imply be reapplied if the condition still holds.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b16e55808dd0">Not all styling rules use this tag system. Som=
e rules are evaluated directly against field values on the work item and ar=
e listed separately below.</p>
<p local-id=3D"6825c4494569">Tag-Based Rules (NEEDS-ATTENTION + FIX:&lt;rea=
son&gt;)</p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrap=
per confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-imag=
e image-left" alt=3D"image-20260305-160026.png" width=3D"468" loading=3D"la=
zy" src=3D"e5acec51300a4e2d591290b2045e7e04cf325e36f76ca180a2cd344922cd8450=
" data-image-src=3D"https://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki/download/att=
achments/8489566320/image-20260305-160026.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationD=
ate=3D1772726430580&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"137" =
data-width=3D"724" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource=
-id=3D"8676081727" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-=
type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image-20260305-16=
0026.png" data-base-url=3D"https://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki" data=
-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-=
id=3D"8489566320" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"31" data-media-=
id=3D"3dc55776-70d7-4bff-b73a-d5145e7777d7" data-media-type=3D"file" height=
=3D"88"></span>
<p local-id=3D"4d907ba31da3"></p>
<p local-id=3D"83a6cab99fa3"><strong>WIP Limit Exceeded =E2=80=94 FIX:WIP-L=
imit </strong><span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard=
(ADO)-WIP-Limit-Exceeded"><span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"WIP-=
Limit-Exceeded"></span></span></p>
<ul local-id=3D"cf7f4babc3c1">
<li local-id=3D"21b5435f4d9a">
<p local-id=3D"02b768ec53ec"><strong>Colour:</strong> Light Yellow</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f7bfde7f-f1b5-42a4-9f76-ed6d623996ee">
<p local-id=3D"e02259e53190"><strong>Explanation:</strong> WIP limits have =
been breached, see <a href=3D"https://emishealthgroup.atlassian.net/wiki/sp=
aces/ECOT/pages/8489566320/Azure+DevOps+Board+ADO#3.4---WIP-Limits" rel=3D"=
nofollow">WIP Limits</a>. This step has exceeded its <strong>per-person WIP=
 limit</strong> (e.g., <strong>Breakdown</strong>, <strong>Implement</stron=
g>, <strong>Validate</strong>). WIP limits cap how many items can be in a w=
orkflow stage at once so that people <strong>finish work before starting mo=
re</strong>, <strong>reduce multitasking/context switching</strong>, and <s=
trong>make bottlenecks visible</strong> when work starts to pile up.</p></l=
i>
<li local-id=3D"eba295e7-f935-41a1-b3c0-4b0bafa3861c">
<p local-id=3D"fbfd7aed24e3"><strong>How to fix:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"d382155a7213">
<li local-id=3D"fe9d10ad5caa">
<p local-id=3D"f74e194479d6">Don=E2=80=99t start/pull anything new into thi=
s step while it=E2=80=99s over the limit.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a5b311da1a94">
<p local-id=3D"d8967136ff2b">Finish or move one of the in-progress items fo=
rward so the count drops to the <a href=3D"https://emishealthgroup.atlassia=
n.net/wiki/spaces/ECOT/pages/8489566320/Azure+DevOps+Board+ADO#3.4---WIP-Li=
mits" rel=3D"nofollow">WIP Limit</a> threshold.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7a5775554b80">
<p local-id=3D"0cd2bb330525">If you must reduce WIP quickly, move the lowes=
t-priority item(s) to Tracked until the limit is met.</p></li>
</ol></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"a1336fecefcb" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-CommonScenarios">=
Common Scenarios</h3>
<h4 local-id=3D"81433b46eef8" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-Sanitycheckwhata=
=E2=80=9Ccard=E2=80=9Drepresents(andre-sizeifneeded)">Sanity check what a =
=E2=80=9Ccard=E2=80=9D represents (and re-size if needed)</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"7f5f7a01fd9d">
<li local-id=3D"caa67305ec59">
<p local-id=3D"da96730cc671">ADO cards represent a unit of delivery/work, n=
ot a 1:1 mirror of ServiceNow items (e.g., RITMs/INCs).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ef36bfbd6a10">
<p local-id=3D"c6d3cbf749b1">If multiple RITMs/INCs share the same implemen=
tation steps and can reasonably be completed as one coherent chunk, combine=
 them into ONE ADO card.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d4041f53154e">
<p local-id=3D"a3a985f2484c">Track the individual RITMs/INCs as tasks on th=
e ADO work item card (e.g., add each RITM/INC as a task/checklist item or c=
learly listed sub-task within the work item), so the board still shows one =
unit of flow while preserving traceability.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c8a4b912d7e7">
<p local-id=3D"03391935f453">If the combined work is too large, split it in=
to multiple ADO cards by outcome/step so each card remains a manageable chu=
nk, then pull them in one at a time to stay within WIP.</p></li>
</ul>
<h4 local-id=3D"7059328dd741" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-Sizecardsusingthe=
Breakdown[Doing]definition">Size cards using the Breakdown [Doing] definiti=
on</h4>
<ul local-id=3D"147613ed13af">
<li local-id=3D"958da619c686">
<p local-id=3D"35ab73a1a301">A card should be =E2=80=9Cbroken down=E2=80=9D=
 into a piece of work sized to: =E2=80=9CMinimum 30 minutes =E2=80=93 Max 3=
 days-ish=E2=80=9D.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d5e6af1c4bc4">
<p local-id=3D"a7cbe5e6a518">Use this as the rule of thumb for whether to c=
ombine or split work:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b7764d4b468f">
<li local-id=3D"35a492d38334">
<p local-id=3D"fa5b183a2148">If multiple RITMs/INCs can be completed within=
 that size window using the same implementation, they can usually be combin=
ed into one card (with each RITM/INC added as a task on the card).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"04531777a93e">
<p local-id=3D"1546993c2845">If not, split until each card fits the Breakdo=
wn sizing.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"c7e7aa24fdab">
<p local-id=3D"ae551dd15b08"><strong>Expedite Item Overdue =E2=80=94 FIX:Ex=
pedite-Age</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"556654d2fe3c"><strong>Colour:</strong> Light Yellow</p>
<p local-id=3D"c03b6935c751">Explanation: This item has been sitting in the=
 Expedite swimlane for longer than the permitted threshold. Expedite items =
are meant to move quickly through the board; if they stall they risk blocki=
ng other work and defeating the purpose of the lane.</p>
<p local-id=3D"4503d0c7c1b0"><strong>How to fix:</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"da7a458bfeb8">Review the item immediately =E2=80=94 identify=
 why it has stalled.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f3c00c15845f">Resolve the blocker, escalate, or re-assess wh=
ether the item genuinely warrants Expedite priority.</p>
<p local-id=3D"25f6d71ed17f">Once it progresses or is moved out of the Expe=
dite lane, the tags will be removed on the next scheduled run.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"e3566f7e5d59">
<h3 local-id=3D"46ce48a4a937" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-LastResponsibleMo=
mentReached=E2=80=94FIX:LRM">Last Responsible Moment Reached =E2=80=94 <cod=
e>FIX:LRM</code></h3>
<p local-id=3D"3bd1ec17a429"><strong>Colour:</strong> Light Yellow</p>
<p local-id=3D"cb1efc640904"><strong>Explanation:</strong><br>
This item is still sitting in the <strong>Breakdown</strong> column even th=
ough its <strong>Start Date</strong> has arrived or already passed. This ru=
le only applies to items with <strong>Class of Service =3D Fixed</strong>.<=
/p>
<p local-id=3D"39e63f680e1a">The <strong>Start Date</strong> represents the=
 <strong>Last Responsible Moment (LRM)</strong> =E2=80=94 the point at whic=
h the item should be picked up to avoid delaying delivery or removing usefu=
l options. If that date has been reached, the work should no longer be wait=
ing in Breakdown.</p>
<p local-id=3D"2546a27f8f55">If the item is <strong>assigned</strong> and t=
he LRM is <strong>today or in the past</strong>, that is a strong signal th=
at someone has effectively picked it up already, but has not actually start=
ed moving it through the workflow. That defeats the purpose of having an LR=
M, which is to make the commitment to start visible and actionable.</p>
<p local-id=3D"92d3eec0653f">A work item is tagged with <code>NEEDS-ATTENTI=
ON</code> and <code>FIX:LRM</code> when <strong>all</strong> of the followi=
ng are true:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"03e0e831-dfdd-46c6-bf2b-c5e48fe96cc8">
<li local-id=3D"3761ff2c-0128-498f-b8c8-e2d97cd19b70">
<p local-id=3D"516f2fca9e11">Board column is <strong>Breakdown</strong></p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"523abf2c-3bb9-4556-a140-49ab00b2ec0b">
<p local-id=3D"a1b9179ee5fb">Class of Service is <strong>Fixed</strong></p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"4d04b07d-f3cb-40a9-b6c4-2f57f39d87e8">
<p local-id=3D"f5066d61d8dc">Start Date is <strong>today or earlier</strong=
></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"cfdc342745e4">A work item will <strong>not</strong> receive =
this tag when any of the following are true:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"02c649d5-0c48-45ff-9845-0d2f07b67f1b">
<li local-id=3D"a906f393-a0b6-4456-bf53-a0aa906a0bc2">
<p local-id=3D"36250c1dcfd0">Class of Service is blank or not <strong>Fixed=
</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a5645f4c-6675-4300-b003-3adda203ea36">
<p local-id=3D"7d04f64629a4">Board column is not <strong>Breakdown</strong>=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8559ef83-04a1-487f-9157-dfec44c53d2c">
<p local-id=3D"cf4dc94c7a97">Start Date is blank</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"53a416bc-f100-47b7-9fdc-0cb5ab65032f">
<p local-id=3D"096d6f004948">Start Date is in the future</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c094b642a8da"><strong>How to fix:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"1c984f97-1ebb-4428-9ca7-c74e3cc5a5b7">
<li local-id=3D"e2ff41ef-8fdc-4f24-8757-96c075d18cf3">
<p local-id=3D"86298895ba35">If the item is ready to begin, <strong>pull it=
 out of Breakdown and start the work</strong>.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"30727d48-cfbd-4b2c-9ba7-40d8b44173be">
<p local-id=3D"9b7989de442d">If the item should not be started yet, <strong=
>review whether the Start Date is still correct</strong> and update it if n=
eeded.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9ca064e2-0737-4dae-b4f4-0de0085b062b">
<p local-id=3D"df423d93c234">If the item is blocked or cannot yet proceed, =
<strong>make that visible by moving it to the appropriate swimlane/state</s=
trong> rather than leaving it in Breakdown.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a4991164-6fba-4404-aea8-608219849848">
<p local-id=3D"3efbf3633e4f">If the item is no longer a genuine <strong>Fix=
ed</strong> commitment, <strong>review whether its Class of Service is corr=
ect</strong>.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c6b72781b559"><strong>Why this matters:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"8fc0e253-83a2-4d53-9e4f-51eb8bad0db6">
<li local-id=3D"d98685d5-7ea1-475e-bb2a-fb3f1469463c">
<p local-id=3D"d0895c5fa769">Ensures <strong>Fixed</strong> date commitment=
s are actively reviewed at the point they need a decision.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f41a31bf-8094-4709-a9f3-d593318b0ef2">
<p local-id=3D"8bf9edad9d06">Prevents work from appearing unstarted when, i=
n practice, someone has already committed to it.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"498114a0-e6bd-4161-8765-ec95e9cb8ec2">
<p local-id=3D"c3a8fea09ecd">Keeps the <strong>Breakdown</strong> column fo=
cused on work that is genuinely being prepared, not work that should alread=
y be in progress.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3dee58e4-0431-4cef-9a33-f15ef90dee70">
<p local-id=3D"a2983fd03f64">Makes missed or stale start commitments visibl=
e early, so they can be acted on before they become delivery issues.</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"e0707cfab01c">
