 data-media-id=3D"a0446f47-c51c-45c1-8d0a-3cf5b38061f0" data-media-type=3D"=
file" height=3D"151"></span>
<ul local-id=3D"f5967a3e-cfd0-4d2f-805b-3bba184d3f6b">
<li local-id=3D"6cec7e2f-83f1-4fba-be83-389d57ddbd29">
<p local-id=3D"117c358f-9fef-4687-a6f4-2cc5ff1a937e"><strong>Colour:</stron=
g> Grey</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e76b5bfa-002c-403d-aec1-27becebcfc7e">
<p local-id=3D"4ba36a0b-cf52-461e-934c-e798176e0b4f"><strong>Explanation:</=
strong> The item has a Fixed CoS but no associated start date (which is use=
d for <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://availagility.co.uk/2010/04=
/06/defining-the-last-responsible-moment/" rel=3D"nofollow">Last Responsibl=
e Moment</a>)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6850b212-c797-48a5-87dc-905d92eea61c">
<p local-id=3D"bfacf417-8156-43c3-9851-c1ef6dada4c8"><strong>How to fix:</s=
trong> Add the correct start date as an LRM.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"df129a89-3f94-4302-99e9-50c78c2451aa">&nbsp;</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"fd0ee5c16563" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.6-Tags">3.6 - T=
ags</h2>
<p local-id=3D"7dd25cb03336">Tags provide an additional layer of classifica=
tion that helps the team analyse trends, identify recurring issues, and sup=
port clear storytelling during incident reviews and continuous improvement =
discussions.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"e05cd092d5e0" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-WhyTagsAreUseful"=
><strong>Why Tags Are Useful</strong></h3>
<ul local-id=3D"1dcc6772-d353-4c99-a1ca-0c21f3a288be">
<li local-id=3D"708aa30a-3734-43d3-b923-1a0280079a5d">
<p local-id=3D"9a49e654e477"><strong>Reporting &amp; Analytics:</strong> Ta=
gs allow us to group work items and identify patterns across pieces of work=
, incidents, or themes (e.g., delays, dependencies, repeat blockers).</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"d560004d-b742-413a-9d24-907231c0b784">
<p local-id=3D"9225385c5acd"><strong>Telling the Story:</strong> When revie=
wing workloads or escalations, tags provide narrative context, they help hi=
ghlight what types of issues we are dealing with most often and whether our=
 processes are protecting the team.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1fd1e929-4c82-49f7-9af0-0653570df96d">
<p local-id=3D"c02f3902c023"><strong>Trend Monitoring:</strong> Over time, =
tags make it easier to identify whether certain categories of issues are in=
creasing or decreasing.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"45fcc6a1624a" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-Tag:ReactingBefor=
eAssessing">Tag: ReactingBeforeAssessing</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ab312a32881b">We=E2=80=99ve seen situations in the past wher=
e technical resource are pulled into P3 incident calls without any evidence=
 the issue is related to their area - This can disrupt ongoing work and pla=
ce avoidable pressure on the team. If you feel you=E2=80=99ve received an e=
scalation without due diligence being done first, please add the tag to the=
 work item:</p>
<p local-id=3D"ffbac4b76b48"><strong>ReactingBeforeAssessing</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"65e7caf3a5d8">This tag helps us track when the team is being=
 involved prematurely, and it provides visibility into:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"5c70e819-286e-4a48-9d43-b4ade2ad2b84">
<li local-id=3D"f559558b-1bb4-4334-984e-5b3e10be6480">
<p local-id=3D"287a5fba693d">Where escalation paths may be bypassing initia=
l diagnosis</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d488df3d-2c4f-4db4-99a6-56807e64bfb7">
<p local-id=3D"d2f6fd3ffa84">Whether there is a visibility or observability=
 gap causing other teams to escalate too early</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"55c15d63-8ebe-4ab0-ad7f-37714b7e5e24">
<p local-id=3D"d2f018e9030b">Whether we need clearer ownership boundaries o=
r better triage documentation</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"edd72a8eb474"></p>
<p local-id=3D"31cceb1b5ece">Over time, reviewing items marked with this ta=
g will help us understand whether:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"a5513bf1-82ad-4e51-b8f1-737d1d20889e">
<li local-id=3D"79bfdf13-326f-41b9-b4a0-2a4cac36dcc1">
<p local-id=3D"d732e87db4a9">Processes need tightening</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6a8f81f9-b717-4f97-8704-31ecbb4a6e6a">
<p local-id=3D"33f5381becec">Monitoring or alerting needs improvement</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"c9405b3f-a8fe-4db4-ab58-2accc58d1331">
<p local-id=3D"513f00efda5a">Other teams need support or training</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"1429b16cf582" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-Tag:KTLO-Assist">=
Tag: KTLO-Assist</h3>
<p local-id=3D"34f6a9d69858">Sometimes members of the commercial outcome te=
ams pick up KTLO/SIPS work to help reduce pressure on the KTLO team. When t=
his happens, please add the tag:</p>
<p local-id=3D"7b7a5c14592c"><strong>KTLO=E2=80=91Assist</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"172d687e12fa">This tag helps us track when KTLO delivery rel=
ies on support from outside the core KTLO team, providing visibility into:<=
/p>
<ul local-id=3D"74d4850a-d852-4519-b4fe-0f6f10327de3">
<li local-id=3D"6be8ab2c-8bf1-4cae-a1ea-6f3818dec4b3">
<p local-id=3D"10758f96da22">How often commercial teams are being used to s=
upplement KTLO capacity</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3116a00c-d443-4e6b-85dc-76f35c603ab9">
<p local-id=3D"25bd10500505">Whether KTLO workload is consistently exceedin=
g available team capacity</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"011eb496-0ed7-4a8e-b27f-58e83cf0203a">
<p local-id=3D"ac82289386e1">Whether prioritisation, automation, or SIP wor=
k may need revisiting</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"2fe51376fea2">Over time, reviewing items marked with this ta=
g will help us understand whether:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"98ebc590-366b-4bc0-b61e-3aa8adfc22b5">
<li local-id=3D"0932580e-1d40-4d74-9cc0-9710c9a4bc79">
<p local-id=3D"0c0fba14aca1">KTLO demand is increasing or becoming unbalanc=
ed</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f6d4d870-e343-4b8f-b0c8-2c8bfba51e50">
<p local-id=3D"d36456d9c0c3">We need to adjust resourcing or planning</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"84773b7c-79cc-4a4f-bdba-a13736360862">
<p local-id=3D"83333b133b73">Further improvements are needed to reduce oper=
ational load</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"19ed638c6af8" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-Tag:PoorPlanning"=
>Tag: PoorPlanning</h3>
<p local-id=3D"cc86da3043ea">This tag should be used when work arrives <str=
ong>last minute</strong> and <strong>should reasonably have been planned ea=
rlier with better notice</strong>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b36a17a07639">If a request or escalation is reactive due to =
a lack of forward planning, insufficient engagement, or avoidable late noti=
ce, please add the following tag:</p>
<p local-id=3D"5fa63dd2f6a8"><strong>PoorPlanning</strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"f2d28f5481fe">This tag helps us identify and evidence situat=
ions where:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"beb790b2-709a-4ea3-ad15-d93f7970324e">
<li local-id=3D"5ce9ec44-cc7c-496d-9a87-e79234ed6fb8">
<p local-id=3D"059f6852ccfb">Work could have been scheduled or communicated=
 earlier</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"176d5c6d-9587-46cf-9bfb-ae203f05ecaa">
<p local-id=3D"24b9d6e88c56">Late notice has caused unnecessary disruption =
to planned delivery</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8c169c22-4d66-410f-8029-bda7c848a617">
<p local-id=3D"7ecd51f3baf8">Preventable urgency is introduced due to misse=
d planning opportunities</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"2073736fde44">Over time, reviewing items marked with this ta=
g will help us understand whether:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"f8752ec2-9600-4a76-8cb1-0ace64583de1">
<li local-id=3D"664e5d14-b2c1-4add-afda-466c19ed365c">
<p local-id=3D"39c6610436a5">Intake and planning processes need improvement=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"82b8c244-10a2-4f30-85da-5dfc1ed037bb">
<p local-id=3D"b73540bb7d32">Expectations around notice periods need to be =
clearer</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4f4967fd-2ecc-43f3-aed5-ad3791c94073">
<p local-id=3D"be10e17e4ed3">Teams need support to engage earlier in delive=
ry cycles</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"2331586d1a21" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.7-Reporting">3.=
7 - Reporting</h2>
<p local-id=3D"9bd7ab237c49">3.7.1 - Common Dashboards that are in use</p>
<p local-id=3D"ce15af2c7d67"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://dev=
.azure.com/emisgroup/8c9df674-f28f-45e4-a329-90bdccde6820/6a414475-09dc-4d1=
8-8e41-8da10cb439b0/_dashboards/dashboard/98d076d8-8abd-4351-ab6a-e87e17ec8=
a5e" rel=3D"nofollow">PIMS - El Capitan - Overview</a></p>
<p local-id=3D"95bdb78a86a6"></p>
<p local-id=3D"bad4698bfe27"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://dev=
.azure.com/emisgroup/8c9df674-f28f-45e4-a329-90bdccde6820/6a414475-09dc-4d1=
8-8e41-8da10cb439b0/_dashboards/dashboard/db7c2e1e-eb6a-4811-b114-f93d618fa=
cb5" rel=3D"nofollow">Out of Hours Work and On Call</a></p>
<h2 local-id=3D"8b59b441338b" id=3D"AzureDevOpsBoard(ADO)-3.8-S&amp;BAreaPa=
ths">3.8 - S &amp; B Area Paths</h2>
<p local-id=3D"08070f4c3264">Due to Storage and Backup being aligned to dif=
ferent outcome teams, please ensure your work on the El Capitan board is vi=
sible across the wider organisation.</p>
<p local-id=3D"717ad01fdb36">When setting the <strong>Area Path</strong>, s=
elect the relevant Storage or Backup area for the appropriate outcome team =
(e.g. Snowdon, Blanc, El Capitan). This will ensure the work is correctly s=
urfaced on the El Capitan board.</p>
<p local-id=3D"9f3482ac7f8a">Please ensure you are using the Planned and Un=
planned work cards.</p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper imag=
e-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-=
embedded-image image-center" alt=3D"image-20260618-142237.png" width=3D"468=
